title: Accidently dropped my Google pixel 4a 5g in the toilet ( slipped out of my hoodie pocket )
content:
I've turned off my phone for about ten minutes, I did put a bit of twisted up tissue down the jack port which soaked up a lot of liquid and wiped down the whole phone. Didn't realised that doing so isn't advisable untill looking it up. 

The phone was half submerged for like two seconds before I got it out and immediately started whipping it down with tissue. Usb port has been automatically disabled, what should I do now?
